 
<p>
The federal appeal court placed onerous restrictions on mifepristone.
It will be available in principle, but obstructed by
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/apr/13/mifepristone-abortion-pill-to-remain-available-in-us-with-restrictions">senseless
restrictions</a>.
<p>
They include a reimposed requirement for an in-person visit to a
doctor.  In addition, the court arbitrarily cut it its use at 7 weeks
of pregnancy.  Many women don't learn they are pregnant that early, so
this will compel millions to have surgical abortions.
<p>
<a href="https://www.commondreams.org/news/5th-circuit-abortion-pill-ruling">More info</a>.
<p>
People
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/apr/13/online-interest-abortion-pills-mifepristone">stocked up on mifepristone</a>
in case they will need it later.
<p>
It is urgent to ramp up the underground networks that obtain
mifepristone and convey it to women who need it.

 